sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant LLS as Llama Stack Server<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    participant vLLM as vLLM Inference<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant vLLME as vLLM Embedding<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI FMS<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant VectorDB as Vector DB<br/>(Milvus/PGVector/Qdrant)
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipelines<br/>HTTP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: OpenAI-compatible Chat Completion (via vLLM)

    Client->>+LLS: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: OAuth2 JWT (optional)
    LLS->>+vLLM: Forward inference request<br/>Auth: Bearer Token<br/>TLS: configurable
    vLLM-->>-LLS: Completion response
    LLS->>PG: Store inference record<br/>5432/TCP Password auth
    LLS-->>-Client: JSON response

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: RAG with Vector Search

    Client->>+LLS: POST /v1/vector_io/query<br/>Auth: OAuth2 JWT (optional)
    LLS->>+VectorDB: Query vector store<br/>Port/TLS varies by backend
    VectorDB-->>-LLS: Similar documents
    LLS->>+vLLME: Embed query text<br/>Auth: Bearer Token<br/>TLS: configurable
    vLLME-->>-LLS: Embedding vector
    LLS->>+vLLM: Generate completion with context<br/>Auth: Bearer Token<br/>TLS: configurable
    vLLM-->>-LLS: RAG-augmented response
    LLS-->>-Client: JSON response

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 3: Safety-guarded Inference

    Client->>+LLS: POST /v1/inference/chat_completion<br/>Auth: OAuth2 JWT (optional)
    LLS->>+TrustyAI: Safety check (pre-inference)<br/>TLS: optional (FMS_SSL_CERT_PATH)<br/>Auth: Certificate
    TrustyAI-->>-LLS: Safety verdict
    alt Safety PASS
        LLS->>+vLLM: Forward inference request<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        vLLM-->>-LLS: Completion response
        LLS->>+TrustyAI: Safety check (post-inference)
        TrustyAI-->>-LLS: Output safety verdict
    else Safety BLOCK
        Note over LLS: Request blocked by guardrails
    end
    LLS-->>-Client: Response (or safety block)

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 4: Model Evaluation via Kubeflow

    Client->>+LLS: POST /v1/eval/run<br/>Auth: OAuth2 JWT (optional)
    LLS->>+KFP: Submit evaluation pipeline<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    KFP->>S3: Read/write eval artifacts<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: AWS IAM
    KFP-->>-LLS: Pipeline run status
    LLS-->>-Client: Evaluation results
